node.text:
Thicc, creamy & spiced with chilli. Recipe below! Have a great weekend ✨

3 cups/750ml @besproud Unsweetened Pea Milk

1 Vanilla Pod, split down the middle & seeds extracted

1 cup/100g Dark Chocolate, chopped small

3 tbs Cacao Powder 

1/2 tsp Ground Cinnamon 

Pinch Dried Chilli Flakes 

3 tbs Maple Syrup or Sugar of your choice

3 tbs Cornflour 

1/2 cup/125ml @besproud unsweetened Pea Milk

Pinch Sea Salt 

Method -

Gently heat the milk in a medium-sized saucepan, with the vanilla pod & seeds.

When the milk is simmering remove the pod, then whisk in the cacao, cinnamon, chilli, maple & chopped chocolate. 

Add the cornflour to a mixing bowl and add the 1/4 cup of milk and whisk together until smooth. 

Whisk the cornflour mixture into the hot chocolate. You will gradually see it thicken up. If it thickens too much just let it down with a little extra milk. 

Add the salt, then serve. 

I topped mine with some sproud barista milk froth, grated chocolate & chilli flakes.

node.text:
never thought I’d enjoy gardening so much but I wish I started sooner I’ve learnt that growing your own can be done anywhere really on the smallest of balconies or even window sills, so I could of grown food on my little London balcony!! The positives are endless, its better for the environment, pesticide free & you will end up eating fresher, tastier and healthier in season produce. This new love for gardening is one of the factors & ingredients in the pot of my new found happiness and contentment. I used to hear the phrase “growing your own food is like printing your own money” & after seeing the abundance of ingredients i’ve managed to grow in a short space of time with just a few seeds and some soil, that statement has been proven to me. The coming months I hope will bring so many more big harvests! 
Its inspired me to have a vegetable garden next to my future restaurant. 
Gaz❤️
